  <title id="km135496">Management Utility Reference</title>
  <shortdesc>Describes the command-line management utilities provided with Greenplum
    Database.</shortdesc>
  <body>
    <p>Greenplum Database uses the standard PostgreSQL client and server programs and provides
      additional management utilities for administering a distributed Greenplum Database DBMS.
      Greenplum Database management utilities reside in <codeph>$GPHOME/bin</codeph>.
      <note>When referencing IPv6 addresses in <codeph>gpfdist</codeph> URLs or when using numeric
        IP addresses instead of hostnames in any management utility, always enclose the IP address
        in brackets. For command prompt use, the best practice is to escape any brackets or put them
        inside quotation marks. For example, use either:<codeph>\[2620:0:170:610::11\]</codeph> or
          <codeph>'[2620:0:170:610::11]'</codeph>.</note></p>
    <p>The following are the Greenplum Database management utilities.</p>
